01/09/2003
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The deputy chief of mission at the US Embassy, Tina Kaidanow, predicted Sunday (31 August) that efforts by local and international authorities to arrest suspected war criminals hiding in BiH would produce results shortly. 
She reiterated the US government's commitment to arresting and punishing war criminals. 
Kaidanow, who recently arrived in Sarajevo, is serving as embassy charge d'affaires in the temporary absence of US Ambassador Clifford Bond. 
(BHTV1, BBC - 31/08/03)
